review_blob: Properly bottle conditioned brett saison. Wonder yellow body with distinctive horse blanket nose. Overall a pleasant beer to drink.
Orange citrus, piney, and a slight note of garlic come off the nose. Taste is smooth bitterness with slight malt sweetness. Overall a good beer. Fits in well with the other west coast IPAs

The brett funkiness stands well with the fruitiness contributed by the hops in the aroma. Brett is the dominant flavor backed up sweet fruity notes. Beautiful beer; clear with nice lacing. Overall a nice saison!
Light and crisp. Nice spiciness from German noble hops. Very well lagered for an unfiltered beer. Nice dry finish. Excellent pilsner.

Wonderful orange hue and lacing. The nose was present as soon as the beer was put in front of me. Fruity, piney, resinous. Im assuming more of the excellent Nelson hop presence that we have all become accustomed to at La Cumbre
Wonderful chocolate nose. Coats the tongue like oil. Bursts of burnt sugars and raisin. Delicious beer.
First wiff of this batch is catty, lemon and floral background. This batch is much lighter than previous batches of dank. Nice hoppy burst to the tongue with a balanced malt body. Excellent
Notes of pear and a slight spiciness. Slight orange hue appearance with a wonderful dry saison finish.
